section.section:
"Community association" means a Maryland nonprofit association, corporation, or other organization that:
Is comprised of at least 20% of the total number of households as members of a local community that consists of 40 or more individual households as defined by specific geographic boundaries in the bylaws or charter of the community association;
Requires, as a condition of membership, the payment of monetary dues at least annually;
Is operated primarily for the promotion of social welfare and general neighborhood improvement and enhancement;
Has been in existence for at least 1 year when it files suit under this section;
Is exempt from taxation under § 501(c)(3) or (4) of the Internal Revenue Code; and
Is in good standing.

"Local code violation" means a violation under the following provisions of the Anne Arundel County Code or under any applicable code relating to the following provisions incorporated in the Anne Arundel County Code by reference:
Article 11 - Crimes and Punishments;
Article 12 - Animal Control;
Article 14 - Environmental Health;
Article 16 - Licenses and Permits; and
Article 22 - Housing Maintenance and Occupancy Code.

text.section:
An action to abate a nuisance may be brought under this section and § 4-401 of the Courts Article by:
The State's Attorney for Anne Arundel County;
The County Attorney for Anne Arundel County;
A community association within whose boundaries the nuisance is located; or
The City Attorney for the City of Annapolis.

section.section:
The notice shall specify:
The nature of the alleged nuisance;
The date and time of day the nuisance was first discovered;
The location on the property where the nuisance is allegedly occurring; and
The relief sought.
